defaultThe shortfall 
defaultin QIPP impacts on the overall financial performance of NHS England. From an assessment of risks and mitigations for the current financial year, NHS England has identified a continued imbalance of financial risk between individual CCGs and between CCGs and
default direct commissioning, with the direct commissioning financial position being the more fragile. In year the risks have been largely mitigated; however, whil
defaulte
default the risks arising have a recurrent impact into future years the sources of mitigation are largely non-recurrent.
