default26
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe Department and NHS England have a key role to play in setting out and driving the case for transformational change. For example, the Secretary of State has challenged the NHS to go ‘paperless’ by
default 2018, highlighting the potential benefits for patients and for taxpayers. The Mandate to NHS England set objectives for it to lead the health and care system in driving better integration of services; and the Government will hold NHS England to account fo
defaultr its performance. However, this transformation cannot be imposed from the top. Engagement on specific local service changes needs to be locally led, and it is CCGs and their local partners that are best placed to understand the needs of their communities 
defaultand the
default opportunities for improvement.
default27
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIt is vital for organisations to work collaboratively to communicate the case for transformational change and to deliver it: both to benefit patients and to improve efficiency. Continued protection of health funding d
defaultoes not mean that all services should remain unchanged. The NHS must adapt and evolve 
defaultto meet the challenges of future demographic trends a
defaultnd rising demand expectations.
default28
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe Government’s modernisation of the NHS will enable commissioners to make changes th
defaultat will deliver real improvements in quality through commissioning that is driven by clinical insight, patient choice and a focus on improving outcomes. This will promote greater integration of services at the local level, including a more coordinated appr
defaultoach to assessment, care planning and care management. Together with increased patient choice and a more rigorous and transparent system for regulating providers, this modernisation will provide much stronger incentives and opportunities to deliver more in
defaulttegrated, personalised and preventive care.
