default100
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe 2012 Act that created NHS England also makes it independently responsible for allocating the budgets for commissioning NHS services. This was done to prevent any perception of political interference in the
default way that money is distributed between different parts of the country, although the Mandate can set out the high level aims for the allocation process.  The current mandate, for instance, requires the allocation of resources to have regard to equal access 
defaultfor equal need, draw on independent advice and take account of the importance of stable funding.  Allocation decisions also need to be consistent with NHS England’s legal duties, in particular to have regard to equality of access to and outcomes from healt
defaulthcare.
default101
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAssessing the effectiveness of allocation decisions is challenging. For instance, it is difficult to isolate the marginal effect of more or less funding on outcomes.  Also, managers strive to manage to their allocations, meaning that the allocations
default are only one factor in determining the financ
defaultial health of an organisation.
default102
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe design of the process for reaching decisions is therefore critical in delivering a financial allocation that is as effective as possible.  NHS England has adopted an allocatio
defaultn process that has clear objectives, uses the best independent advice and places reliance on evidence-based approaches complemented by judgement where appropriate.  These are all features that have been preserved from the previous PCT allocation process an
defaultd which the Public Accounts Committee supported during their landscape review of allocations process across the public sector.
