default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe approach proposed by ACRA is based on current u
defaulttilisation of services: due to data constraints, this is based on hospital utilisation data rather than health services more broadly.  This is then adjusted for factors that affect utilisation, but are not linked to need, such as proximity to a provider.  
defaultHowever, this still leaves a possible gap in estimating need where need is systematically unmet.  This is recognised as one of the key challenges for a utilisation based model.
